 (50,9,'Javascript',2,1,'<p align=\"center\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"></p><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><br></h2><ul style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><li>JS Switch</li><li>JS Popup Boxes</li><li>JS Functions</li><li>JS For Loop</li><li>JS While Loop</li><li>JS Break Loops</li></ul><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">Learning Target</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use multiple selections using switch selection structure.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use for and do/while repetition structures to execute statements in a program repeatedly.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the break and continue program control statements.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the logical operators.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"text-align: start;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">Discussion</font></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">The switch Multiple-Selection Structure</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; JavaScript provides the switch multiple-selection structure to handle a series of decisions in which a variable or expression is tested separately for each of the values it may&nbsp; assume and different actions are taken.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The switch structure consists of a series of case labels and an optional default case. When the flow of control reaches the switch structure, the controlling expression in the parentheses following keyword switch is evaluated. The value of this expression is compared with the value of the case labels, starting with the first case label. If a match occurs, the statements for that case are executed. If no match occurs between the controlling expressions value and the value in case label, the statements in the default case execute.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The break statement at the end of a case causes control to immediately exit the switch. The break statement is not required for the last case in the switch structure ( or the default case when it appears last) because program control automatically continues with the next statement after the switch structure.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">The general format of switch selection structure:</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; switch (<em>variable</em>)</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; case&nbsp;<em>n</em>:</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; statement;</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; break;</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">The for Repetition Structure</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The for repetition structure handles all the details of counter-controlled repetition.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">Counter-controlled repetition requires:</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The&nbsp;<em>name&nbsp;</em>of a control variable (or loop counter).</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The&nbsp;<em>initial value</em>&nbsp;of the control variable.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The&nbsp;<em>increment (or decrement)&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;by which the control variable is modified each time through the loop ( also known as&nbsp;<em>&nbsp;each iteration of the loop).</em></font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The condition that tests for the&nbsp;<em>final value</em>&nbsp;of the&nbsp; control variable to determine whether looping should continue.</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">The general format of for repetition structure:</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: start;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"2\">for (&nbsp;<em>initialization; loopContinuationTest; increment</em>&nbsp;)</font></span></h2><h2 style=\"font-weight: normal; text-align: st