 (75,1,'Propositional Logic',0,0,'<p><b>Logic</b>&nbsp;is the basis of all mathematical reasoning, and of all automated reasoning.</p><p><b>Proposition</b>&nbsp; - is a declarative sentence</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - truth value (either true or false)</p><p><br></p><p>Examples:</p><ol><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 1. Seoul is the capital of South Korea. (<b>PROPOSITION: </b>TRUE)</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 2. Rose is the national flower of the Philippines. (<b>PROPOSITION: </b>FALSE)</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 3. Please close the door. (<b>NOT PROPORTION:&nbsp;</b>Since it is not a declarative sentence)</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 4. Pass your paper. (<b>NOT PROPOSITION:&nbsp;</b><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Since it is not a declarative sentence</span>)</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 5. Listen carefully.&nbsp;(<b style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">NOT PROPOSITION:&nbsp;</b><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Since it is not a declarative sentence</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">FIVE COMPOUND PROPOSITION</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Logical Connectives</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- <b>Negation ( ~ ) </b>is not the case that</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; Example:</li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>P: </b>Seoul is the capital of South Korea.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>~P: </b>Seoul is not the capital of South Korea.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - <b>Conjunction</b>&nbsp;<b>() </b>and</li></ol><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Example:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>P: </b>Kathleen is beautiful</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>Q: </b>Kimberly is lovable.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>P()Q: </b>Kathleen is beautiful and Kimberly is lovable</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - <b>Disjunction ( V ) </b>or</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Example:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>P: </b>Kathleen is on the badminton team</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>Q: </b>Jerica is on the table tennis team</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>PVQ:</b><b style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</b><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">Kathleen is on the badminton team or&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">Jerica is on the table tennis team</span></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - <b>Implication / conditional statement</b>&nbsp; &nbsp; (---&gt;) If p (antecedent premise), then q (consequent solution)</p><p><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>*</b> -p ---&gt; -q (<b>inverse</b>)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>* </b>q ---&gt; p (<b>converse</b>)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; * -q ---&gt; -p (<b>contrapositive</b>)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Example:</p><p>&nbsp;&n