v><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;P: Kathleen is beautiful.<br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Q:&nbsp; Kimberly is lovable.<br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;PQ: Kathleen is beautiful and Kimberly is lovable.&nbsp;<br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<b>Disjunction </b>(  ) or<br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Example:</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;P:&nbsp; Kathleen is on the badminton team.<br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Q: Jerica is on the table tennis team.<br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;PVQ: Kathleen is on the badminton team or Jerica is on the table tennis team.<br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<b>&nbsp;Implication/ conditional statement</b>&nbsp; &nbsp; () If p (antecedent premise), then q (consequent solution).</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;p  q (<b>inverse</b>)<br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;q  p (<b>converse</b>)<br></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;q  p (<b>contrapositive</b>)</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Example:<br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;P: Kathleen learns discrete mathematics.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Q:&nbsp; Kathleen will find a good job.<br></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PQ: Kathleen learns d