 (78,1,'Propositional Logic',0,0,'<p><b>Logic</b>  is the basis of all mathematical reasoning, and of all automated reasoning.</p><p><b>Proposition</b>- is a declarative sentence.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;-truth value (either true or false).</p><p>Examples:</p><ol><li>Seoul is the capital of South Korea.&nbsp; ( PROPOSTION: TRUE)</li><li>Rose is the national flower of the Philippines. (PROPOSITION: FALSE)</li><li>Please close the door. (NOT PROPOSITION: Since it is not a declarative sentence)</li><li>Pass your paper. (NOT PROPOSITION: Since it is not a declarative sentence )</li><li>Listen carefully. (NOT PROPOSITION: Since it is not a declarative sentence)</li><li><br></li></ol><p><b>FIVE COMPOUND PROPOSITION</b></p><p><b>Logical Connectives</b></p><p><b>Negation </b>(~ ) () is not the case that</p><p>Example:</p><ol><li>P:<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Seoul is the capital of South Korea.</li><li>~P:<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> Seoul is not the capital of South Korea.</li></ol><p><br></p><p><b>Conjunction </b>() and</p><p>Example:</p><ol><li>P: Kathleen is beautiful.</li><li>Q:&nbsp; Kimberly is lovable.</li><li>PQ: Kathleen is beautiful and Kimberly is lovable.&nbsp;</li></ol><p><b>Disjunction </b>(  ) or</p><p>Example:</p><ol><li>P:&nbsp; Kathleen is on the badminton team.</li><li>Q: Jerica is on the table tennis team.</li><li>PVQ: Kathleen is on the badminton team or Jerica is on the table tennis team.</li><li><br></li></ol><p><b>Implication/ conditional statement</b>&nbsp; &nbsp; () If p (antecedent premise), then q (consequent solution).</p><ol><li>p  q (inverse)</li><li>q  p (converse)</li><li>q  p (contrapositive)</li></ol><p>Example:</p><ol><li>P: Kathleen learns discrete mathematics.</li><li>Q:&nbsp; Kathleen will find a good job.</li><li>PQ: Kathleen learns discrete mathematics then she will find a good job.</li><li><br></li></ol><p><b>Biconditional Statement</b> () p if and only if q.</p><p>Example:</p><ol><li>P:&nbsp; You can take the flight.</li><li>Q: You buy a ticket.</li><li>PQ: You can take the flight if and only if you buy a ticket.</li></ol><p><br></p><p><b>TRUTH TABLE</b></p><p><b></b></p><p style=\"text-align: center; \">Truth table for the ~p</p><p style=\"text-align: center; \">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><br></p><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>P</td><td>~p</td></tr><tr><td>T</td><td>F</td></tr><tr><td>F</td><td>T</td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><br></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><div>Truth table for the p  q.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>p</td><td>q</td><td>p V q</td></tr><tr><td>T</td><td>T</td><td>T</td></tr><tr><td>T</td><td>F</td><td>F</td></tr><tr><td>F</td><td>T</td><td>F</td></tr><tr><td>F</td><td>F</td><td>F</td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><div><br></div></div><div><br></div>');
